SIMPLE: optography
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Optography
<hw>Op*tog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Opt</ets>ic + <ets>-graphy</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The production of an optogram on the retina
by the photochemical action of light on the visual purple; the fixation
of an image in the eye. The object so photographed shows white on a
purple or red background. See <cref>Visual purple</cref>, under
<er>Visual</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Optometer</ent>⟦br⟧
